The paper deals with the mitigation of nonlinear distortion caused by power amplifiers in OFDM systems, which is a common problem in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the study of communication systems and their limits. The paper also involves communication systems and signal processing, which suggests the category cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). The proposed algorithm involves probability estimation, which is a common topic in cs.SI (Signal Processing). The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves simulations and performance evaluation, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
